# Design source of truth

The **single canonical source** of game rules is [`docs/design/DESIGN.md`](../../docs/design/DESIGN.md).

Detailed rationale and alternatives: [`docs/design/decisions/`](../../docs/design/decisions/) (DDR files).

Things not yet decided: [`docs/design/open-questions.md`](../../docs/design/open-questions.md).

## Deprecated

- [`BASE_RULES.txt`](../../BASE_RULES.txt) — **DO NOT EDIT**, history only.
- [`formatted_rules.html`](../../formatted_rules.html) — **DO NOT EDIT**.

If you find a discrepancy between the legacy files and DESIGN.md:

- **DESIGN.md wins**, no exceptions.
- If the legacy content might be useful as design input, **ask the user**
  whether to record its archaeological value in a new DDR before silently
  overriding or ignoring it.

## Linking convention

Each section of DESIGN.md cites the relevant DDR (e.g., "see DDR-0010"). When
new design content is added to DESIGN.md, **either** there is already a DDR
covering it, **or** a new DDR is created at the same time.
